**TJX BEAT its Q4 FY2025 pre-tax margin guidance by approximately 70 basis points (vs. the high end of its guided range).**

**Details:**

1. **Guidance:** In its Q3 FY2025 earnings release (November 20, 2024), TJX guided to a fourth quarter FY2025 pretax profit margin of **10.8% to 10.9%**.

2. **Actual result:** In its Q4 FY2025 earnings release (February 26, 2025), TJX reported a fourth quarter pretax profit margin of **11.6%** (pretax income of $1,889M ÷ net sales of $16,350M = 11.55%, rounded to 11.6%).

3. **BPS difference (beat):**
   - vs. high end of guidance (10.9%): 11.6% − 10.9% = **+70 bps**
   - vs. midpoint of guidance (10.85%): 11.6% − 10.85% = **+75 bps**
   - vs. low end of guidance (10.8%): 11.6% − 10.8% = **+80 bps**

TJX itself confirmed in the press release that the Q4 pretax margin was "above the high-end of its plan by 0.7 percentage points" (i.e., a **70 bps beat**), driven primarily by lower-than-expected inventory shrink expense and expense leverage on above-plan sales, partially offset by higher incentive compensation accruals.

**Conclusion: TJX beat its Q4 FY2025 pretax profit margin guidance by ~70 bps (relative to the 10.9% high end of the guided range; 75 bps vs. the midpoint).**

