Micron (MU) BEAT its Q3 fiscal 2024 GAAP gross margin guidance by approximately 140 basis points.

Details:
- Guidance: When Micron reported Q2 FY2024 results on March 20, 2024, it guided FQ3-24 GAAP gross margin to 25.5% ± 1.5% (midpoint = 25.5%).
- Actual: For Q3 FY2024 (quarter ended May 30, 2024, reported June 26, 2024), Micron delivered a GAAP gross margin of 26.9% (gross margin of $1,832M on revenue of $6,811M; $1,832/$6,811 = 26.90%).

Calculation:
Beat = Actual − Guidance midpoint = 26.9% − 25.5% = 1.40 percentage points = 140 basis points.
(Using unrounded actual of 26.897%, the beat is ~139.68 bps, i.e., approximately 140 bps.)

Note: The actual of 26.9% also came in just below the very top end of the guidance range (25.5% + 1.5% = 27.0%), meaning Micron beat the midpoint by 140 bps and landed near the high end of its guided range.

